====================
What I learned:
====================
- A cloud of comets, the Oort Cloud encloses our solar system (the 2nd line of our cosmic address)

- Rogue planets are frozen planets that may contain water, or life

- Virgo supercluster is a collection of billions of galaxies

- Giordano Bruno was an Italian monk who read and theorized about the universe. This was outlawed by the Catholic Church, and as a result, he was kicked out from the church.
  *He theorized that the universe was infinite
  *He believed that the universe was filled with other suns orbited by other planets
  *Believed that an infinite God would create an infinite universe
  *Excommunicated from churches in Italy, Germany, Switzerland, England. 
  *Imprisoned for 8 years in Italy
  *Burned at the stake for not recanting

- After the Big Bang, gravity pulled together clumps of helium and hydrogen to create stars

- In the last 14 seconds of the "calender of the universe" was all of recorded history 

- 30,000 years ago, our ancestors invented astronomy to aid their survival

- Carl Sagan was a 20th century scientist who contributed a lot to our current understanding of the universe 

